Geographic origin: Lexington, Cleveland County, Oklahoma, United States
Notes on original: No. 783. Peach, Cytospora canker. Sent in by Robert E. Thacker, Lexington, Okla, May 12, 1914. The upper part of this dying twig shows the Cytospora or Valsa in abundance. Am inclined to question the canker lower down on the twig.
Name: Prunus persica
